(check mise.toml, e2e/testutil/, e2e/*.go files)\\n3. How is it passed to individual tests?\\n\\nSearch for patterns like \\\"go build\\\", \\\"TestMain\\\", \\\"binary\\\", \\\"entirePath\\\", \\\"entireBin\\\" in the e2e/ directory and mise configuration files.\",\"agentId\":\"af0f06b832fce1754\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_014J67vcNd1oUuteGCT1iiJZ\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01QgFjpWUzwU2sTUBR7Enb9a\",\"uuid\":\"fb44606b-1783-4837-b23d-2d2d271bdb7b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T01:06:47.084Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"fb44606b-1783-4837-b23d-2d2d271bdb7b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d9f0a13a-2256-4ef2-a6ed-7fe605e55655\",\"version\":\"2.1.58\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"ticklish-zooming-robin\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_016tt3LaPu8zLjNJUbpPwtSC\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# E2E Tests\\n     2→\\n     3→End-to-end tests for the `entire` CLI against real agents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode).\\n     4→\\n     5→## Commands\\n     6→\\n     7→```bash\\n     8→mise run test:e2e TestFoo              # run filtered (or omit filter for all agents)\\n     9→mise run test:e2e:claude TestFoo       # Claude Code only\\n    10→mise run test:e2e:gemini TestFoo       # Gemini CLI only (sequential, avoids rate limits)\\n    11→mise run test:e2e:opencode TestFoo     # OpenCode only\\n    12→go build ./...                         # compile check (no agent CLI needed)\\n    13→```\\n    14→\\n    15→**Do NOT run E2E tests proactively.** They make real API calls that consume tokens and cost money. Only run when explicitly asked.\\n    16→\\n    17→## Structure\\n    18→\\n    19→```\\n    20→e2e/\\n    21→├── agents/       # Agent abstraction (Agent interface, tmux sessions, concurrency gates)\\n    22→├── bootstrap/    # CI pre-test setup (auth config, warmup)\\n    23→├── entire/       # `entire` CLI wrapper (enable, rewind, etc.)\\n    24→├── exploratory/  # Experimental tests, not run by CI\\n    25→├── tests/        # Blessed test files (run by CI)\\n    26→└── testutil/     # Repo setup, assertions, artifact capture\\n    27→```\\n    28→\\n    29→## Key Patterns\\n    30→\\n    31→- Every test uses `testutil.ForEachAgent` which runs it per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling.\\n    32→- All operations go through `RepoState` (`s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`) so they're logged to `console.log`.\\n    33→- Use the `entire` package for CLI interactions, not raw `exec.Command`.\\n    34→- Skip tests pending CLI fixes with `t.Skip(\\\"ENT-XXX: reason\\\")`.\\n    35→\\n    36→## Adding a New Agent\\n    37→\\n    38→1. Create `agents/<name>.go` implementing the `Agent` interface.\\n    39→2. Register it in `init()` with `Register(&YourAgent{})`.\\n    40→3. Add a `Bootstrap()` method for any CI-specific setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    41→4. Add a `RegisterGate(\\\"<name>\\\", N)` call if concurrency needs limiting.\\n    42→5. Add a `test:e2e:<name>` task in `mise.toml`.\\n    43→6. Add the agent to `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` matrix and `e2e-isolated.yml` options.\\n    44→\\n    45→## Environment Variables\\n    46→\\n    47→| Variable | Description | Default |\\n    48→|----------|-------------|---------|\\n    49→| `E2E_AGENT` | Agent to test (`claude-code`, `gemini-cli`, `opencode`) | all registered |\\n    50→| `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` | Path to a pre-built `entire` binary | builds from source |\\n    51→| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | Timeout per prompt | `2m` |\\n    52→| `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` | Set to `1` to preserve temp repos after test | unset |\\n    53→| `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` | Override artifact output directory | `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>` |\\n    54→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for Claude Code | — |\\n    55→| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required for Gemini CLI | — |\\n    56→\\n    57→## Debugging Failures\\n    58→\\n    59→Artifacts are captured to `e2e/artifacts/` on every run (git-log, git-tree, console.log, checkpoint metadata, entire logs). Set `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1` to preserve the temp repo — a symlink appears in the artifact dir pointing to it.\\n    60→\\n    61→Use the `debug-e2e` skill (`.claude/skills/debug-e2e/`) for a structured workflow when investigating failures.\\n    62→\\n    63→### Reading artifacts\\n    64→\\n    65→- `console.log` — full operation transcript including agent stdout/stderr\\n    66→- `git-log.txt` — commit history at time of failure\\n    67→- `git-tree.txt` — working tree state\\n    68→- `entire-logs/` — internal CLI logs\\n    69→\\n    70→### Fixing flaky tests\\n    71→\\n    72→When a test passes on retry but failed once, the problem is usually agent non-determinism, not a CLI bug. Common patterns:\\n    73→\\n    74→- **Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting**: The model output contains \\\"Does this look right?\\\" or \\\"Should I proceed?\\\". Fix: append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation, just make the change.\\\" to the prompt.\\n    75→- **Agent wrote to wrong path or created extra files**: Fix: be more explicit about exact file paths and what _not_ to do.\\n    76→- **Agent committed when it shouldn't have**: Fix: add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to the prompt.\\n    77→- **Checkpoint wait timeout**: `WaitForCheckpoint` or `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom` exceeded deadline. Fix: increase the timeout argument.\\n    78→\\n    79→To diagnose: read `console.log` in the failing test's artifact directory. Compare what the agent actually did vs what the test expected.\\n    80→\\n    81→## CI Workflows\\n    82→\\n    83→- **`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`** — Runs full suite on push to main. Matrix: `[claude, opencode, gemini]`.\\n    84→- **`.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml`** — Manual dispatch for debugging a single test. Inputs: agent + test name filter.\\n    85→\\n    86→Both workflows run `go run ./e2e/bootstrap` before tests to handle age